The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Metlife India Insurance has launched Metlife integrated voice response application (MIVRA), a technology platform, which would help customers obtain information about their insurance plan and other details round the clock. MIVRA, designed to expand the access of opportunities to more customers, raise the efficiency bar of the service levels and reduces costs for the organisation, the insurer said in a statement.                            
	 Ramsarup Industries Ltd recorded an increase in profit after tax of 36 per cent at Rs 59.42 crore for the year ended March 31, 2008, against Rs 43.56 crore last year. Exports jumped 34 per cent to Rs 95.73 crore from Rs 71.44 crore. The net income stood at Rs 1581.85 crore for the year ended March 31, 2008, a 21 per cent jump from Rs 1,306.02 crore.                             
	 The board of Sunil Hitech Engineers Ltd has announced a dividend of 12 per cent on equity shares of Rs 10 each subject to the shareholders approval. For the year ended March 31, 2008, the companys profit after tax stood at 177.62 per cent year-on-year to Rs 21 crore from Rs 7.56 crore.                             
	 Tata Chemicals Society for Rural Development has inaugurated an Okhai retail outlet at Himalaya Mall, Ahmedabad. Okhai promotes the handicrafts made by the women in the Okhamandal region in Gujarat.                             
	 ICICI Bank has launched B2-branch-free banking, which will offer information through a single interface to facilitate banking transactions over the internet. Apart from easy access and anytime banking, customers opting for the facility can benefit from zero charges and no minimum balance.                            
	 General Motors (GM) India has launched a limited period offer for the Chevrolet Spark at a starting price of Rs. 2.66 lakh (ex-showroom, Delhi).                            
	 Volvo has introduced 9400 intra-city bus, delivering the first lot to the Andhra Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation, which will increase the latters fleet size to 20.                             
	 Fastrack has launched the Summer 2008 collection of wrist gear and eye gear in Calcutta. The watches are priced between Rs 595 and Rs 2,495. The sunglasses are priced between Rs 695 and Rs 1,995.                             
	 Finolex Industries has introduced its UV-stabilised and lead free plumbing system in selected parts of the country.                             
	 Hindustan Unilever Ltd has launched Ponds skin lightening collection with lycopene. The products are priced from Rs 50 onwards.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
